# Laravel API Resource Generator

**Command**: `/laravel:api-resource [name] [options]`

**Description**: Generates a complete API resource with model, migration, controller, resources, validation, tests, and OpenAPI documentation.

## Usage

```bash
/laravel:api-resource User --auth
/laravel:api-resource Product --with-images --paginated
/laravel:api-resource Order --relationships="belongsTo:User,hasMany:OrderItem" --versioned
/laravel:api-resource BlogPost --fields="title:string,content:text,published_at:datetime"
```

## Options

- `--auth` - Include authentication endpoints (login, register, profile)
- `--versioned` - Create versioned API (v1, v2, etc.)
- `--paginated` - Include pagination helpers
- `--with-images` - Add image upload capabilities
- `--with-search` - Include search functionality
- `--with-filters` - Add filtering capabilities
- `--with-sorting` - Include sorting options
- `--fields="field:type,..."` - Define model fields
- `--relationships="type:Model,..."` - Define model relationships
- `--rate-limit=60` - Set rate limiting (requests per minute)
- `--soft-deletes` - Add soft deletes support
- `--cacheable` - Add caching layer

## Generated Files

### Core API Files
- `app/Models/{Name}.php` - Eloquent model with API optimizations
- `database/migrations/{timestamp}_create_{table}_table.php` - Migration
- `app/Http/Controllers/Api/{Name}Controller.php` - API controller
- `app/Http/Resources/{Name}Resource.php` - JSON resource transformer
- `app/Http/Resources/{Name}Collection.php` - Collection resource
- `app/Http/Requests/Api/Store{Name}Request.php` - Store validation
- `app/Http/Requests/Api/Update{Name}Request.php` - Update validation

### Testing & Documentation
- `tests/Feature/Api/{Name}ControllerTest.php` - API endpoint tests
- `tests/Unit/{Name}Test.php` - Model unit tests
- `database/factories/{Name}Factory.php` - Model factory
- `storage/api-docs/{name}-endpoints.yaml` - OpenAPI documentation

### Optional Files (Based on Options)
- `app/Http/Controllers/Api/Auth/{Name}AuthController.php` - Auth endpoints (if --auth)
- `app/Http/Middleware/RateLimit{Name}.php` - Custom rate limiting (if custom rate limit)
- `app/Http/Filters/{Name}Filter.php` - Query filters (if --with-filters)
- `app/Services/{Name}Service.php` - Business logic service layer
- `app/Observers/{Name}Observer.php` - Model observer for API events

## Implementation

### Step 1: Generate Core API Structure
```php
// API-optimized model
class Product extends Model
{
    use HasFactory, SoftDeletes, Cacheable;

    protected $fillable = [...];
    protected $hidden = ['created_at', 'updated_at'];
    protected $casts = [...];

    // API-specific scopes
    public function scopeWithFilters($query, $filters) { ... }
    public function scopeWithSearch($query, $search) { ... }
}
```

### Step 2: Create API Controller
```php
class ProductController extends Controller
{
    public function __construct()
    {
        $this->middleware('auth:sanctum');
        $this->middleware('throttle:api');
    }

    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $products = Product::query()
            ->withFilters($request->get('filters', []))
            ->withSearch($request->get('search'))
            ->paginate($request->get('per_page', 15));

        return ProductCollection::make($products);
    }

    public function store(StoreProductRequest $request)
    {
        $product = Product::create($request->validated());

        return ProductResource::make($product)
            ->response()
            ->setStatusCode(201);
    }

    // ... other CRUD methods
}
```

### Step 3: Generate JSON Resources
```php
class ProductResource extends JsonResource
{
    public function toArray($request)
    {
        return [
            'id' => $this->id,
            'name' => $this->name,
            'price' => $this->formatted_price,
            'description' => $this->description,
            'images' => ImageResource::collection($this->whenLoaded('images')),
            'category' => CategoryResource::make($this->whenLoaded('category')),
            'created_at' => $this->created_at?->toISOString(),
            'updated_at' => $this->updated_at?->toISOString(),
        ];
    }

    public function with($request)
    {
        return [
            'meta' => [
                'version' => '1.0',
                'links' => [
                    'self' => route('api.products.show', $this->id),
                ]
            ]
        ];
    }
}
```

### Step 4: Generate Comprehensive Tests
```php
class ProductControllerTest extends TestCase
{
    use RefreshDatabase;

    protected function setUp(): void
    {
        parent::setUp();
        $this->actingAs(User::factory()->create());
    }

    public function test_can_list_products()
    {
        Product::factory()->count(5)->create();

        $response = $this->getJson('/api/products');

        $response->assertOk()
            ->assertJsonStructure([
                'data' => [
                    '*' => ['id', 'name', 'price', 'description']
                ],
                'meta' => ['current_page', 'total', 'per_page'],
                'links' => ['first', 'last', 'prev', 'next']
            ]);
    }

    public function test_can_create_product_with_valid_data()
    {
        $data = [
            'name' => 'Test Product',
            'price' => 99.99,
            'description' => 'A test product'
        ];

        $response = $this->postJson('/api/products', $data);

        $response->assertCreated()
            ->assertJsonFragment($data);

        $this->assertDatabaseHas('products', $data);
    }

    public function test_cannot_create_product_with_invalid_data()
    {
        $response = $this->postJson('/api/products', []);

        $response->assertUnprocessable()
            ->assertJsonValidationErrors(['name', 'price']);
    }

    // ... more comprehensive test methods
}
```

### Step 5: Generate OpenAPI Documentation
```yaml
paths:
  /api/products:
    get:
      summary: List products
      tags: [Products]
      parameters:
        - name: page
          in: query
          schema:
            type: integer
        - name: per_page
          in: query
          schema:
            type: integer
            maximum: 100
        - name: search
          in: query
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: List of products
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  data:
                    type: array
                    items:
                      $ref: '#/components/schemas/Product'
                  meta:
                    $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaginationMeta'
    post:
      summary: Create product
      tags: [Products]
      requestBody:
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateProductRequest'
      responses:
        201:
          description: Product created
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Product'
```

## Advanced Features

### Authentication Integration
```php
// With --auth option, generates complete auth system
class UserAuthController extends Controller
{
    public function register(RegisterRequest $request)
    {
        $user = User::create([
            'name' => $request->name,
            'email' => $request->email,
            'password' => Hash::make($request->password),
        ]);

        $token = $user->createToken('auth-token')->plainTextToken;

        return UserResource::make($user)->additional([
            'meta' => [
                'token' => $token,
                'token_type' => 'Bearer',
            ]
        ]);
    }

    public function login(LoginRequest $request)
    {
        if (!Auth::attempt($request->only('email', 'password'))) {
            return response()->json([
                'message' => 'Invalid credentials'
            ], 401);
        }

        $user = Auth::user();
        $token = $user->createToken('auth-token')->plainTextToken;

        return UserResource::make($user)->additional([
            'meta' => [
                'token' => $token,
                'token_type' => 'Bearer',
            ]
        ]);
    }
}
```

### Advanced Filtering & Search
```php
class ProductFilter
{
    public function apply($query, $filters)
    {
        foreach ($filters as $filter => $value) {
            $method = 'filter' . ucfirst($filter);
            if (method_exists($this, $method)) {
                $this->$method($query, $value);
            }
        }
        return $query;
    }

    protected function filterPrice($query, $value)
    {
        if (isset($value['min'])) {
            $query->where('price', '>=', $value['min']);
        }
        if (isset($value['max'])) {
            $query->where('price', '<=', $value['max']);
        }
    }

    protected function filterCategory($query, $value)
    {
        $query->whereHas('category', function($q) use ($value) {
            $q->where('slug', $value);
        });
    }
}
```

### Caching Integration
```php
class ProductController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $cacheKey = 'products:' . md5(serialize($request->all()));

        $products = Cache::remember($cacheKey, 3600, function() use ($request) {
            return Product::query()
                ->withFilters($request->get('filters', []))
                ->withSearch($request->get('search'))
                ->paginate($request->get('per_page', 15));
        });

        return ProductCollection::make($products);
    }
}
```

## Route Generation

### API Routes
```php
// routes/api.php
Route::group(['prefix' => 'v1', 'middleware' => 'auth:sanctum'], function () {
    Route::apiResource('products', ProductController::class);

    // Additional endpoints based on options
