# Laravel API Resource Generator

**Command**: `/laravel:api-resource [name] [options]`

**Description**: Generates a complete API resource with model, migration, controller, resources, validation, tests, and OpenAPI documentation.

## Usage

```bash
/laravel:api-resource User --auth
/laravel:api-resource Product --with-images --paginated
/laravel:api-resource Order --relationships="belongsTo:User,hasMany:OrderItem" --versioned
/laravel:api-resource BlogPost --fields="title:string,content:text,published_at:datetime"
```

## Options

- `--auth` - Include authentication endpoints (login, register, profile)
- `--versioned` - Create versioned API (v1, v2, etc.)
- `--paginated` - Include pagination helpers
- `--with-images` - Add image upload capabilities
- `--with-search` - Include search functionality
- `--with-filters` - Add filtering capabilities
- `--with-sorting` - Include sorting options
- `--fields="field:type,..."` - Define model fields
- `--relationships="type:Model,..."` - Define model relationships
- `--rate-limit=60` - Set rate limiting (requests per minute)
- `--soft-deletes` - Add soft deletes support
- `--cacheable` - Add caching layer

## Generated Files

### Core API Files
- `app/Models/{Name}.php` - Eloquent model with API optimizations
- `database/migrations/{timestamp}_create_{table}_table.php` - Migration
- `app/Http/Controllers/Api/{Name}Controller.php` - API controller
- `app/Http/Resources/{Name}Resource.php` - JSON resource transformer
- `app/Http/Resources/{Name}Collection.php` - Collection resource
- `app/Http/Requests/Api/Store{Name}Request.php` - Store validation
- `app/Http/Requests/Api/Update{Name}Request.php` - Update validation

### Testing & Documentation
- `tests/Feature/Api/{Name}ControllerTest.php` - API endpoint tests
- `tests/Unit/{Name}Test.php` - Model unit tests
- `database/factories/{Name}Factory.php` - Model factory
- `storage/api-docs/{name}-endpoints.yaml` - OpenAPI documentation

### Optional Files (Based on Options)
- `app/Http/Controllers/Api/Auth/{Name}AuthController.php` - Auth endpoints (if --auth)
- `app/Http/Middleware/RateLimit{Name}.php` - Custom rate limiting (if custom rate limit)
- `app/Http/Filters/{Name}Filter.php` - Query filters (if --with-filters)
- `app/Services/{Name}Service.php` - Business logic service layer
- `app/Observers/{Name}Observer.php` - Model observer for API events

## Implementation

### Step 1: Generate Core API Structure
```php
// API-optimized model
