# Laravel Query Optimizer

**Command**: `/laravel:optimize-queries [options]`

**Description**: Intelligently detects and fixes N+1 queries, optimizes database queries, and implements efficient data loading patterns across your Laravel application.

## Usage

```bash
/laravel:optimize-queries --scan-all
/laravel:optimize-queries --model=User --with-relationships
/laravel:optimize-queries --controller=ProductController --suggest-eager-loading
/laravel:optimize-queries --api-resources --paginate-heavy-queries
```

## Options

- `--scan-all` - Scan entire application for query optimization opportunities
- `--model=ModelName` - Focus on specific model relationships
- `--controller=ControllerName` - Optimize specific controller queries
- `--api-resources` - Optimize API resource queries specifically
- `--with-relationships` - Deep analysis of model relationships
- `--suggest-eager-loading` - Suggest eager loading strategies
- `--paginate-heavy-queries` - Add pagination to heavy queries
- `--add-indexes` - Suggest database index optimizations
- `--cache-queries` - Add intelligent query caching
- `--explain-queries` - Show query execution plans

## Detection & Analysis

### N+1 Query Detection
```php
// BEFORE: N+1 Query Problem
class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $posts = Post::all(); // 1 query

        return view('posts.index', compact('posts'));
    }
}

// In the view: posts.index.blade.php
@foreach($posts as $post)
    <h3>{{ $post->title }}</h3>
    <p>By: {{ $post->user->name }}</p> <!-- N queries (one for each post) -->
    <div>Comments: {{ $post->comments->count() }}</div> <!-- Another N queries -->
@endforeach

// TOTAL: 1 + N + N queries (potentially hundreds!)
```

### Automatic Optimization
```php
// AFTER: Optimized with Eager Loading
class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $posts = Post::with(['user', 'comments'])->get(); // 3 queries total

        return view('posts.index', compact('posts'));
    }
}

// Alternative: Selective eager loading based on usage
class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $posts = Post::with([
            'user:id,name,email', // Only load necessary columns
            'comments' => function ($query) {
                $query->latest()->limit(5); // Only recent comments
            }
        ])->get();

        return view('posts.index', compact('posts'));
    }
}
```

## Advanced Optimization Patterns

### Conditional Eager Loading
```php
class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $query = Post::query();

        // Conditionally eager load based on request
        if ($request->has('include_user')) {
            $query->with('user');
        }

        if ($request->has('include_comments')) {
            $query->with(['comments' => function ($q) {
                $q->with('user')->latest();
            }]);
        }

        // For API: eager load based on requested includes
        if ($request->has('include')) {
            $includes = explode(',', $request->include);
            $validIncludes = ['user', 'comments', 'tags', 'category'];
            $includes = array_intersect($includes, $validIncludes);

            if (!empty($includes)) {
                $query->with($includes);
            }
        }

        $posts = $query->paginate(15);

        return PostResource::collection($posts);
    }
}
```

### Query Optimization with Scopes
```php
class Post extends Model
{
    // Efficient scope for common queries
    public function scopeWithUserAndComments($query)
    {
        return $query->with([
            'user:id,name,avatar',
            'comments' => function ($q) {
                $q->with('user:id,name')
                  ->select('id', 'post_id', 'user_id', 'content', 'created_at')
                  ->latest()
                  ->limit(3);
            }
        ]);
    }

    // Scope for dashboard performance
    public function scopeForDashboard($query)
    {
        return $query->select([
                'id', 'title', 'slug', 'excerpt', 
                'user_id', 'created_at', 'status'
            ])
            ->with('user:id,name')
            ->withCount(['comments', 'likes'])
            ->latest();
    }

    // Scope for API performance
    public function scopeForApi($query)
    {
        return $query->select([
                'id', 'title', 'slug', 'content',
                'user_id', 'category_id', 'created_at', 'updated_at'
            ])
            ->with([
                'user:id,name,email',
                'category:id,name,slug',
                'tags:id,name'
            ]);
    }
}

// Usage in controllers
class PostController extends Controller
{
    public function dashboard()
    {
        $posts = Post::forDashboard()->paginate(20);
        return view('dashboard.posts', compact('posts'));
    }

    public function apiIndex()
    {
        $posts = Post::forApi()->paginate(15);
        return PostResource::collection($posts);
    }
}
```

### Chunk Processing for Large Datasets
```php
class ReportController extends Controller
{
    public function generateUserReport()
    {
        // BEFORE: Memory intensive
        // $users = User::with('posts', 'comments')->get(); // Could load millions of records

        // AFTER: Memory efficient chunk processing
        $report = [];

        User::with(['posts' => function ($query) {
                $query->selectRaw('user_id, COUNT(*) as post_count')
                      ->groupBy('user_id');
            }])
            ->chunk(1000, function ($users) use (&$report) {
                foreach ($users as $user) {
                    $report[] = [
                        'user_id' => $user->id,
                        'name' => $user->name,
                        'post_count' => $user->posts->sum('post_count'),
                        'last_active' => $user->last_login_at,
                    ];
                }
            });

        return response()->json($report);
    }
}
```

### Subquery Optimizations
```php
class ProductController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        // BEFORE: Multiple queries or heavy joins
        // $products = Product::with('reviews')->get();
        // foreach ($products as $product) {
        //     $product->average_rating = $product->reviews->avg('rating');
        // }

        // AFTER: Single query with subqueries
        $products = Product::select([
                'products.*',
                // Subquery for average rating
                DB::raw('(SELECT AVG(rating) FROM reviews WHERE reviews.product_id = products.id) as average_rating'),
                // Subquery for review count
                DB::raw('(SELECT COUNT(*) FROM reviews WHERE reviews.product_id = products.id) as review_count'),
                // Subquery for latest review date
                DB::raw('(SELECT MAX(created_at) FROM reviews WHERE reviews.product_id = products.id) as latest_review_at')
            ])
            ->where('status', 'active')
            ->orderByDesc('average_rating')
            ->paginate(20);

        return ProductResource::collection($products);
    }
}
```

### API Resource Optimization
```php
class PostResource extends JsonResource
{
    public function toArray($request)
    {
        return [
            'id' => $this->id,
            'title' => $this->title,
            'slug' => $this->slug,
            'excerpt' => $this->excerpt,
            'content' => $this->when($request->routeIs('posts.show'), $this->content),
            'status' => $this->status,
            'created_at' => $this->created_at->toISOString(),
            'updated_at' => $this->updated_at->toISOString(),

            // Conditional relationships (only load when already eager loaded)
            'user' => new UserResource($this->whenLoaded('user')),
            'category' => new CategoryResource($this->whenLoaded('category')),
            'comments' => CommentResource::collection($this->whenLoaded('comments')),
            'tags' => TagResource::collection($this->whenLoaded('tags')),

            // Computed attributes (only when needed)
            'comment_count' => $this->when(
                $this->relationLoaded('comments') || isset($this->comments_count),
                $this->comments_count ?? $this->comments->count()
            ),
            'reading_time' => $this->when(
                $request->has('include_reading_time'),
                $this->getReadingTimeAttribute()
            ),

            // Conditional includes based on request
            'full_content' => $this->when(
                $request->has('full_content') && $this->userCan('view', $this->resource),
                $this->content
            ),
        ];
    }

    // Optimize collection queries
    public static function collection($resource)
    {
        return parent::collection($resource)->additional([
            'meta' => [
                'total' => $resource->total(),
                'per_page' => $resource->perPage(),
                'optimizations' => [
                    'eager_loaded' => ['user', 'category'],
                    'query_count' => DB::getQueryLog() ? count(DB::getQueryLog()) : null,
                ]
            ]
        ]);
    }
}
```

## Database Index Optimization

### Index Analysis & Suggestions
```php
// Command analyzes queries and suggests indexes
class IndexOptimizer
{
    public function analyzeQueries()
    {
        $suggestions = [];

        // Analyze slow query log
        $slowQueries = $this->getSlowQueries();

        foreach ($slowQueries as $query) {
            $suggestions[] = $this->suggestIndexForQuery($query);
        }

        // Common index patterns
        $suggestions[] = [
            'table' => 'posts',
            'columns' => ['status', 'created_at'],
            'reason' => 'Frequently filtered by status and ordered by date',
            'migration' => 'Schema::table("posts", fn($table) => $table->index(["status", "created_at"]));'
        ];

        $suggestions[] = [
            'table' => 'users',
            'columns' => ['email'],
            'reason' => 'Login queries always filter by email',
            'migration' => 'Schema::table("users", fn($table) => $table->unique("email"));'
        ];

        return $suggestions;
    }
}
```

### Generated Index Migrations
```php
